 cultural studies as a well as a wider readership interested in the British Museum.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aEthnological museums and collectionszEnglandzLondon. 0aEthnologistszEnglandzLondonvBiography. 7aART / Museum Studies.2bisacsh  aEthnography in the Museum.  aHistory of the British Museum.  aMuseum Memoir.  aVarious Roles of a National Museum.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBerghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2019z978311099772940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781789203035?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781789203035423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781789203035/original  a978-3-11-099772-9  Berghahn Books Complete eBook-Package 2019b2019  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK